text: Grevillea squiresiae is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to a small area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia. The single-stemmed shrub typically grows to a height of that blooms from September to December producing an inflorescence with red flowers. ==See also== * List of Grevillea species ==References== squiresiae Category:Proteales of Australia Category:Eudicots of Western Australia
